subsection.def:
claim (申索) means a
                claim made under section 24 in accordance with section
                25;

ERO (主任) means the
                Electoral Registration Officer within the meaning of section 2(1) of the
                Election Ordinance;

preceding year (對上一年) means, in relation to the compilation of a provisional register,
                the year immediately preceding the year for which the provisional register is being
                compiled;

principal residential address
                    (主要住址) has the same meaning as in
                    section 2(1) of the Election Ordinance;

paragraph.content:
an Existing Villages register or a Market Towns register, the entry of
                        the name and principal residential address of a person in that register;
                            and (5 of 2014 s. 19)

subsection.def:
inclement weather warning day (惡劣天氣警告日) means a working day on which a gale
                warning or a rainstorm warning is in force at any time during the ordinary business
                hours of the Office;

paragraph.content:
a date is prescribed in this Regulation (whether by reference to a specific
                    day of a specific month or to a day otherwise ascertainable under this
                    Regulation) or is fixed under this Regulation;

a date is prescribed by reference to a specific day of a specific month in
                    a provision (former provision) specified in column 1 of the
                    Table;

the ERO is satisfied on reasonable grounds (based on information
                        received in response to the inquiry or otherwise) that the person is
                        dead;

subparagraph.content:
in relation to the compilation of the provisional register for
                            2022—the period beginning on 17 July 2021 and ending on 16 June 2022;
                            or

paragraph.content:
for a period beginning on the date on which the notice under subsection (1)
                    is published in the Gazette and ending on 9 September in the same year; (12 of 2014 s.
                            14)

subsection.def:
publication date (刊登日期), in
                relation to a provisional register, means the date on which a notice relating to the
                register is published in the Gazette under subsection (1);

subparagraph.content:
and has publicly declared an intention to arrange for any person
                            (including a person yet to be specified) to stand as a candidate at a
                            coming election;

subsection.def:
publication date (刊登日期), in
                relation to a final register, means the date on which a notice relating to the
                register is published in the Gazette under subsection (1);

subparagraph.content:
and has publicly declared an intention to arrange for any person
                            (including a person yet to be specified) to stand as a candidate at a
                            coming election;
